    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1616"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1616">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.0144.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>One hour ago Samuel Cantu, former Mayor of Lampasos, Mexico, was enticed to the
                    middle of the international bridge, seized on the American side of the boundary
                    by two Mexican officers, dragged across the boundary and thrown into prison. It
                    is said that he will be shot to-morrow morning. I have already made a protest to
                    the General.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
